General Motors of Canada Ltd said itwill close its Montreal truck centre August 31, due to lowsales volume, putting most of the centre's 131 employees out ofwork.    "The sales volume at the centre has been insufficient tosupport the operation," the company said in a statement.    "With the recently announced joint venture with Volvo tosupply the heavy-duty truck market, customer requirements forthe GM line of light and medium duty trucks will be bettersatisfied by GM dealers located throughout Quebec," the companysaid.    General Motors Canada said it will provide 52 weeks oflayoff benefits for most employees and up to 104 weeks for somesenior employees. Reuter&#3;